projTitle: Crystal Shop SQL Database Design and Development
problemSolvedDescription:
Designed database for a fictional crystal shop, handling tracking of products, customers, reviews, and sales. Developed documentation including diagram of 10+ tables to guide implementation.

As team lead, designed overall requirements, documentation, and initial table diagram. Managed project by splitting and assigning work on diagram design, glossary, crow's foot ERD, and SQL implementation.

Implemented database using SQL, creating tables, constraints and procedures, and inserting data. Developed Java application that uses the terminal to validate user input and handles menu selection to allow use of the database.

Created GitHub issues for each task and assigned work to group members. Researched and implemented quicksort with first element as pivot, random, and median of three.

Created 70 arrays of random integers as sample data to run through each sorting algorithm, with 14 different lengths, using quicksort to produce random order, 50% ordered, 75% ordered, 100% ordered, and 100% reverse ordered for each length.

Tested quicksort using JUnit, tested efficiency of different pivot schemes using sample data, and summarized findings in report.
